column1: Will President Volodymyr Zelensky either flee Ukraine or cease to be its president before 25 November 2022?
column6: ['Foreign Policy', 'Leader Entry/Exit', 'Security and Conflict']
Passage of time.
#BravoZulu
I doubt he will free in the next 3 days, considering the situation on ground right now.
Nov 25th, 2022 is very soon and Zelensky has shown little signs of wanting to give up territory or leave. Most likely scenario where he is no longer leader is his death.
There are only 2 remaining days to meet this condition. Even with greater than even odds of this happening within a year the likelihood of this happening within 2 days are closer to 0 than 1 percent,
Lowering to reflect lowered probability given days left. Base rate is 0.42% probability which is yearly death rate in Ukraine. (or 0.42% *2 /365 ).
Selensky is a popular leader and Russia's soldiers are not prepared for the winter.
Past behaviour is a guide to future performance
Small probability

Ukraine has EU, USA military backing. It is in the economic interest of EU and USA to add Ukraine into the global economy, start a Marshall Plan like in WW2. Russia has a terrible military and won't be able to hold Crimea much longer. There is a very small probability of this happening

Given there is only 4 days left in this forecast and the current stalemate in the Ukraine war this is highly unlikely at this point. Given Russia has not retreated there is still a chance some event may still cause this but the probability is very low at this point.

The chances that Zelenskyy will flee Ukraine due to the ongoing war is slim given that there are only 5 days left in this forecast and there is a stalemate at the frontlines. Zelenskyy could also flee or resign or die or be overthrown due to civil unrest or a coup or an assassination attempt or illness but the likelihood of these outcomes occurring is also slim in such a short time span.
I updated my forecast to be closer to consensus. Also, there is only one week left, and Ukraine carries on repressing the Russian initiative.
Highly unlikely in the next week.
He has been shown to be a great leader, and the war is still in favor for the Ukrainians (not that Russia is ''losing'', just that the outcome they expected was in high probability not achieved).
Less than 10 days to go.
He is winning.

Ukraine has gain momentum in the conflict over the past weeks. President Zelensky seems more determined than ever to see Ukraine gain back all of its territory. This makes any voluntary action to flee or cease to be president highly improbable. Remains the accidental, tragic and other involuntary possibilites that would result in him being no longer president.
President Zelensky has had ample opportunities to flee the country and has chosen not to. I do not believe he will “flee” the country.

President Zelensky has successfully led Ukraine through its defense against Russia incursion and takeover despite tremendous pressures and setbacks. He demonstrates confidence and brazen boldness that has served him well. While I do believe an effort exists to unseat him and he is not always the most popular with certain NATO members, I believe he has staying power, and it is unlikely he will cease to be president by November 25, 2022. I believe it is overconfident to believe Russia and Ukraine are closer to peace talks than they are. The timing isn't right. Advantage is in Ukraine and Zelensky's favor currently, where his cessation as president is concerned. I also don't believe Zelensky has the type of personality to cut-and-run. That's not his style. He has also managed to survive multiple assassination attempts. If he were to cease from power, Ukraine would also fall simultaneously, or that occurrence would be imminent. I see it as unlikely that he will leave voluntarily. He has high poll numbers within Ukraine. His popularity and the high confidence he instills would be difficult to replace. A successful assassination would only make him a martyr and further Ukranian spirit and cause, inspired by the legacy he has personally nurtured on behalf of Ukraine. Strategically, he is unlikely to "flee" or leave the country, as a public event.
No. Not in this Universe.

Not only has Zelensky staked his flag as a person who does not flee his country, but Ukraine is also doing significantly well in its war with Russia. There is no way he is fleeing in the next month. For example, Russia just withdrew from Kherson. The only way I can see Zelensky ceasing to be the Ukrainian president would be if he was killed, but I think there is a less that 1/100 chance that that happens.

I'm a bit late to the game on this one. Given that there are only a few weeks left, Zelensky is firmly in control with a high approval rating, and has demonstrated repeatedly that he is likely willing to die in Ukraine alongside his citizens than flee, I see a 0% chance of this occurring in the next few weeks.

There is not much time left until 25 November, and Zelensky seems to be in firm control of the power. The foreseeable dire winter due to the recent and potential future Russian attacks targeted at the power grid make it very unlikely for any domestic attempt to overturn the current leadership, there are no such foresigns and it would only make the situation worse. The uncertainty of my estimate comes from the constant threat to Zelensky's life, but I think he is and will be fairly well protected.

Very happy to become this certain that Zelensky will be safe. (21 day timeframe has major impact on my level of confidence, of course). Ukraine’s military will presumably have to keep working very hard to protect him far longer than this Question’s timeframe, and I’d even put a very high (90+%) chance that they will succeed for as long as Zelensky’s term in office will extend (2024+, perhaps he’ll even be re-elected?)
He won't flee, and he won't step down, but this is a war, and he might get hit by some missile.

He hasn't fleed yet and there are only 28 days left until 25-Nov-2022. However, if Russia steps up its attacks, he may feel the need to flee to be able to continue to "govern" outside of Ukraine until Russian forces are expelled or a peace agreement is reached.
low probability within next month, but not zero. no rumbling of negative sentiment for the president in the country
While chances of fleeing are very small based on what has happened so far, chances of being injured or killed and no longer being president are somewhat higher.
He showed resolve to remain when the threat to him personally was more imminent earlier this year.
He will live or die in Ukraine.
Just a chicken 1 per Cromwell's rule.
He's got sufficient support to stick around awhile longer.
At worst, he will be a martyr and die in Ukraine/ It will make a great movie
At worst, he will be a martyr and die in Ukraine. It will make a great movie
Goes against his brand.

The crowd's 5% seems a bit high. Russia may luck into specific intelligence on Zelenskyy's location and launch a missile at it, but the odds are remote. The US attempted this in the Iraq war, btw, so it's something that happens: https://www.theguardian.com/world/2003/mar/20/iraq.jamesmeek
Ukraine is winning.
Unless he get killed.

The only way this happens is if Russia makes a big military gain, which won't happen before the muddy season or until the mobilization gains steam. Another option is assassination. But seems like that's not what is on Russia's mind, nor does it have the capability to do this.

Military operations now slowing down for "mud season". Putin's new general in charge of operations appears to prefer hitting soft targets like pedestrian bridges and playgrounds. Hard targets like energy plants and (I presume) key government offices are better protected by anti missile systems. FSB have shown low capacity to organise attacks on key civilian personnel. Chances of a lucky missile strike on Zelensky or targeted assassination before end of this question are now v low. Zero chance of him resigning.
I think these are events that will only happen with a major escalation - use of WMD for example. I think NATO deterrent is enough to prevent Russia from doing that

President Zelensky seems to be dedicated to keeping up the appearance of a strong presidency in the face of the Russian invasion. I doubt he would flee Ukraine now that the fighting is in Ukraine's favor. I believe the only way he would cease to be president by November would be if he is killed by Russian agents, bombardment or a nuclear blast (particularly unlikely).
President Zelensky is too patriotic to flee Ukraine or cease to be its president. He fights for his country and for the people.

Up just slightly because I suspect that Putin and his new general in charge of Ukraine are mulling over whether a tactical (or strategic?) nuclear weapon could kill Zelenskyy (not a typo, that's the correct spelling), and if so, would it do them more harm than good?
Going up on this (temporarily?) given my raised prediction on Russia’s potential use of nuclear weapons - a contingency based on a contingency (so,+1).
Down 5% for passsage of time. I've been mostly above the consensus most of the time.
no way. ride or die
Only if he is assassinated.
I think his life is in increased danger right now, these next two months will be intense given Putin's increased hostilities and failures.
Either flee or cease to be president:

The idea of Zelensky fleeing Ukraine by 25 November seems difficult to imagine since Kiev hasn't been much of a military objective for the Russian Armed Forces and, even if it were to both become one and then promptly fall to the Russian Ground Forces, Zelensky could always move his command post further west, like to Lviv.

Zelensky has enough funds to stay afloat in Ukraine for much longer than 25th of November 2022. He will probably cry again for more money from USA taxpayer in the next few weeks. Joe Biden is eager to shell out lots of money for his Ukrainian profiteering scam. Russia will annex large swathes of Ukraine for a buffer zone from NATO expansion and could possibly bring the warfare to an end by the end of the year leaving Zelensky free to have Drag Queen story time at his local library then retiring and moving to USA to play star 🌟 with the elites of Hollywood.
Down 5% for passage of time.
Time decay. No current reason to think that Zelensky is at greater risk now than he was back in April/May.
Ukraine is on track to win the war.
Just1% per Cromwell's Rule.

Thanks to analysis by @dcoberle @sevedb @dowser @Peijster I don't believe there are any internal threats to Zelensky's political or physical survival at this point. A revenge attack by Russian special forces is possible (Think you're so tough? Ha ha VZ, we got you), however I also believe NATO is streaming Ukraine tons of intelligence daily and would provide ample warning if there were indications. (I have no evidence to back up that assertion; just my firm belief that it is so.)
It is more unlikely now than at the beginning of the conflict.
Down 5% for passage of time. I do wonder about Wagner, et al.
Ukraine appears to have more of an edge on the war while more time has also passed. For both reasons I reduce the % chance to 5%
Time decay
Up 5% at least until a plausible, benign explanation for the accident surfaces.
2 months is a short time, lowering the estimate. But this will happen in 2023/24.
"Will Russia win?" Probably. :(
There's a report that Zelensky was involved in a car accident in Kyiv tonight but there were no serious injuries. No info on whether this was suspicious or provoked.
Time has passed since my last forecast and he still hasn't fled or ceased to be
No reason to believe this.
He's going to die there, whether of old age, or in this war. He's stubborn and isn't going anywhere.
Toma de Jarkov

Counterattack by Ukraine (seems succesful) makes it extremely unlikely Kiev (or Zelensky) will be threatened enough to decide to flee. Special intervention by special forces (which could be alternative threat) by Russia deemed extremely unlikely.
The offensive in Kherson is perceivably going well as seen from Ukrainian social media analysis. This reduces an element of the very small potential that Zelensky will be forced from office.
Russia could win the war outright by then, which would force Zelensky to flee or cease to be its president. Zelensky could also be killed before then.
1. He is determined to win against Russia
Not more probabel than VP ceaseing to be President in Russia during this timeframe.
Posiblemente sea destituido pero cuando finalice el conflicto.

He didn't flee at the start of the conflict, and he's less likely to now after six months. There's a possibility that he will be assassinated before the end of November, but its less likely now than at any point previously in the conflict.

Life must be particularly treacerous for the Ukrainian President. But as time goes by it becomes more and more unlikely. I believe that at the beginning of the "special operation" it was most important to have him down, but right now Putin won't gain much, except public international outrage.
Extremely unlikely in the next three months, given how the war is going. Assuming one in 20 chance over 12 month timeframe, so one in 80 for this question.
Too popular with Ukrainians and the West, and Russia doesn't have the ability to force him to leave.
Short of an assassination he’ll survive as he’s proven to be adept at managing the conflict (internal support) and difficult to kill despite Russia’s best efforts (external threat).
Short of an assassination he’ll survive as he’s proven to be adept at managing the conflict (internal support) and difficult to kill despite Russia’s best efforts (external threat).

This question highly depends on Ukraine's ability to hold substantial parts of its territory until this date. Even though Russia is obviously the bigger military power, the conflict has shown so far, how poorly prepared its army is and how challenging it can be to invade such a massive country, when people aren't on your side. Hence, from my point of view, the Ukrainian armed forces will make it an absolute nightmare to take control over major cities like Kiev. Also, the military missions in Afghanistan have shown, how easy it is for rebellious groups to hide even under the worst circumstances. Thus, I believe Ukraine's forces will fight until the very last sqm of territory is under full Russian control - not just officially occupied - which leaves Zelensky with a higher chance to survive hidden somewhere than when he decided to stay in Kiev at the beginning of the war.
(no change) https://lite.cnn.com/en/article/h_ec768fb70e8c8d6e114c02d73ffb2ea7

Zelensky's position has not faced recent challenges, recent military successes have likely improved his standing in Ukraine further. His planned offensive operation in southern Ukraine (Kherson) doe present the potential for challenges to his leadership if it is perceived to be unsuccessful. For these reasons I am lowering the probability, but will leave some room for things to get more challenging for the President - next review will be around late-Sept, early Oct, to allow the outcome of offensive operations, unless some major developments occur before then.
(up 2%) Car bomb and Wagner Group.
Have broken into various scenarios, to which I've assigned probabilities:
I have assumed he will not be assassinated

This is now a slow methodical war, there will be no decisive losses or gains before 25 Nov 22. If there is a risk to Zelensky it will be from former members of his government who have now been removed or if he seems to be losing western support as the year ends, the latter less likely this year.

Energy crisis in Europe could put political pressure on PM to negotiate with russia which he may be unwilling to do. Could precipitate a leadership change. So far western governments have mostly backed him though so base case is they continue to support
I can't see him fleeing or stepping down. Just a remote chance of a lucky artillery or missile strike.
(no change) Regardless of who caused it, if Zaporizhzhia has a significant nuclear release, there will almost certainly be a change in management. Comparison class: Chernobyl.

It depends on how much closer to Kyiv, Russian forces advance, in addition President Zelensky's position will be determined by the Ukrainians themselves, do they approve of President Zelensky's overall handling of the war? Is a essential factor.
He will not flee nor lose the war. Opposition could get stroger or the west stops its support.
I'm going down to 1% instead of zero on account of Cromwell's Rule https://www.statisticshowto.com/cromwells-rule/

I do not see Zelensky fleeing the country ever. I do not see him ceasing to be its president in the next 3 1/2 months - unless Russia successfully wins the war. I see Ukraine will and effort lasting beyond 11/2022 and do not see any movement for Zelensky's ouster.
(no change) Zaporizhzhia!
reduceing due to a more stable constellation.
Zelensky had multiple options to flee and didn't; typically when governments fall (e.g. Afghanistan) those who flee leave very soon. Zelensky will go down with his ship.

Prolonged Russo-Ukranian stalemate, deadline approaches. Odds keep diminishing until the situation drastically changes (i.e. Russian complete mobilization, nuclear weapon deployment, other countries formally joining the war, etc.)
https://voxeurop.eu/en/ukrainian-kutuzov-general-zaluzhny-why-are-his-tactics-spotlight/
(no change) Interesting but I don't have access to information one way or another:
Updating for passage of time. The war drags on. President Zelensky remains unlikely to resign.
Close to frozen front / stalemate. Unlikely for Kiev to be threatened. Firm control of govt. due to war and rally round the flag.
President Volodymyr Zelensky is the Winston Churchill of the 21st century.

Increasing this potential once more, but by larger percentage points this time, after President Zelensky made two further high profile sackings this weekend. There are very few details of the circumstances emerging, but the situation does again highlight some challenges that he seems to be facing.
Up 1% on news of some Ukrainian sackings. It has got to be complicated. VP might actually have been sainted if he hadn't gone rogue. ;-)

Zelensky seems firmly in control, and his death or removal might not even be a Russian goal given it would further tensions and escalate the conflict even more (and provoke more a response from the West). Russia could be content with the state of play and consolidating territory in the Donbas. However, this is a volatile situation and something unexpected could certainly occur.
Russia is (and will) increase violence in Ukraine, and will also, most likely increase its efforts to assassinate him. As sad it is to say.
Russia has intensified their march on Ukraine over the last weeks. I put the probability slightly higher based on non-political reasons he would cease to be president.
Zelensky sacked Ambassadors. Could mean that there is some tension in Kiew.

Zelensky recently sacked a number of Ambassadors, suggesting that there are some internal government quarrels. Although still only a remote likelihood, these events show that it is not all plain sailing for the Ukrainian president.
Unless he is assassinated then I don't foresee this happening.
The war has settled into a stalemate. But he could be assassinated
He could die / be killed

Slightly increasing the probability here, as some of the conscription issues are causing the potential for frictions between Zelensky, and the Ukrainian population on one side and the MoD on the other
Maintaining estimate
Adjusting downward as the war has settled into a stalemate.

(no change) When the death and destruction totals are assessed, perhaps he should be replaced by a "Quisling." Of course it would not be "fair" but step back and consider other on-going hot wars in various places. The 21st century has had a bumper crop of unfairness.
Up 2%. Gas
zelensky is a loyal russian federation military officer russia took control of ukraine during the orange revolution
He could die.
(no change) FWIW:
Kyiv seems relatively safe, bar the occasional missile attack so there is less risk of him being deposed by force.
At this point, Zelensky proved to everybody that he will never flee Ukraine.
I'm going to raise just slightly as Ukraine is apparently in a serious materiel shortage, and may be sustaining more casualties also
my thought is zelensky is no longer with us because he was identified as a Russian soldier and his subversion campaign in Ukraine failed

there are already precedents for the departure of oligarchs and presidents from Ukraine. The Russian army is advancing. When approaching Kiev, the invasion of Poland and the dismemberment of Ukraine, Zelensky will be forced to leave the country or will be killed

The longer the war goes the higher the risk for him. Russia has made advances in the East recently and has captured more territory than I understand was expected given all the earlier reports of Russia's botching of the operation in so many respects. As much as Ukraine has been uniquely heroic in its fight and resistance, Russia is still advancing.
Political splits within Ukraine are notoriously partisan but President Zelensky remains the best leader possible both internally and externally for Ukraine.

There is already a precedent for the departure of a number of politicians and oligarchs from Ukraine. This is especially characteristic of the successes of the Russian army at the initial stage of the operation. if the Russian troops continue to advance, Zelensky will be forced to leave Ukraine, probably to the territory of Poland, with which an alliance is being created.

Fingers crossed that Zelensky’s ability to visit his troops on the front line is a sign that he is now much safer than during the initial phases of the war. (There is of course another interpretation: “Fingers crossed that it’s not reckless hubris for Zelensky to be out and about, and that further public appearances don’t give Russian agents chances that they wouldn’t otherwise have.”)
- Throughout the conflict, Zelensky has not fled no matter how bad things have gone

(no change and I'm sure I'm repeating my lame idea) VZ might take one for the team and step down if it meant a "reasonable" deal with VP. He could go back to his day job while waiting for his Nobel Prize.
Decreasing probability since time has passed and the war increasingly looks like a stalemate. Of course, it's a long way to November, and the situation can change suddenly.
Only if he died/was killed before 25 November 2022.
Zelensky will outlast Putin.

Going down with probability of Zelensky ceasing to be the President. My thinking has been - to win, Putin may go all-in to decapitate Ukraine and kill its popular President as invasion is stalling. It still may happen, but may open a hunt on Putin himself. By a lot of players. Will he risk that? I doubt it. Aligning better with the crowd.

$40bn aid package authorised from the US, and $3.8bn in arms, including so many Javelin missiles that the US is running low having burned through 7 years supply in two months of donations. Multiple billions are also coming from other western countries, alongside arms and equipment from German, UK and others. The West simply won't allow Ukraine to fall.
Long way to go until November.
The war is continuing in the south east. But I still think it's dangerous for him.
War continues and this may indeed be the most dangerous time since the war's onset. Slightly higher prediction for the longer window.
I would see this as extremely unlikely.
No he said he would fight to the end in honor of his grandpa who was Jewish in the Holocaust.
Time decay

The main drivers are over a battle in Donbass region. If Putin gets Ukrainian army in cauldron there, there is a significant chance Ukraine may go for surrender. If this does NOT happen, Putin may use all tools necessary to get victory some other way - one of them is beheading of Ukrainian leadership. All previous attempts of assassinations will pale in comparison.

Everything so far to me indicates Zelensky has no intention of leaving Ukraine. This may change as the situation develops - I think the Zelensky Govt leaving Ukraine would be widely perceived as the end of effective resistance to Russian advances, and therefore unlikely before November 2022, without significant Russian progress.

Reducing chances (forecast essentially reflects assessed chance of assassination). If Putin had the capability, he’d probably have done it by now. (He’s reportedly tried, and he surely has capability to try again, but he doesn’t seem to have the capability to succeed, thankfully.)
Strong leader, well regarded.

While I think it is possible for Zelensky to change his stance on remaining in-country during the war (he could come to believe that the risk of his death or capture would be worse for Ukraine than his leaving the country), I consider it fairly unlikely. He seems to believe that his clear public presence bolsters Ukrainian morale and acts as a powerful media image to gain global support, and he is dependent on both to survive Russia's invasion.
Highly unlikely that the Russians ever take Kyiv, therefore highly unlikely that President Zelensky ceases to be President or flees.

Right now he is a national hero and will not leave voluntarily. If he were assassinated it would make him a martyr but would also be a psychological blow for Ukraine so I believe Russia will continue to try and kill him.

I think it is very unlikely that Russia is capable of taking over Kyiv with its military, so he won't flee. The only way I see for him to stop being president is being killed, either due to assassination or because of a nuclear strike.
About double the chances I assigned to a May 25 end date. Again, I suspect death from the war, a very rare accident or an assassination to be the leading causes.

The Europeans and NATO will not allow Ukraine to loose the war … that does not mean they will win, but that the minimum goal will be a cease fire. After all the atrocities there will likely not be an end of war with a peace treaty in the next decade … and all of that will have no influence on the position of the current president.
Not forecasting he will leave Ukraine but death by assassin is reason for a low probability.
Probability of targeted assassination by Russian forces cannot be ruled out. Still a long time to go until November.
I don't think him fleeing is very probable, but there already were several attempts on his life.

He could cease to be president by natural death, assassination, fleeing the country, resigning voluntarily or as part of a brokered peace deal, or being ousted by Russia. It's very unlikely that he'd flee given that he hasn't so far and that move would tarnish his reputation / legacy (<1% chance). It's also very unlikely that Ukrainians would ask for his resignation given his popularity as a war time leader (<1% chance). I think assassination / death by bombing / special forces strike is a non-zero possibility even in the next 5 months, maybe 2%. Further, there's still a <3% chance the entire country could fall before November despite Russia's revised stance of wanting to 'liberate' the Donbas region. A brokered peace deal where he is forced to resign in order to preserve a majority of Ukraine's geographic sovereignty is also a possibility (~2%).

Not likely to flee but continues to be a high target for Russia, has so far shown remarkable skill and resilience at managing the crisis but it seems to me things will only get more difficult with time given the amount of destruction around and the increasing needs of the country.
Zelle sky is not likely to flee, though he has the means to do so if capture seems likely.

Fleeing seems improbable (<1%). If the wording "cease to be president" includes a successful assassination/attack costing his life, probability is somewhat higher while still remote. Russian focus seems on eastern Ukraine for now, but long-range missiles or covert ops may eventually succeed.
I am a little higher than on my previous forecast.

Killing Zelensky seems very low. And it wouldn't cripple Ukrainian defence or give territory gains but bring only political and diplomatic costs. Contrary to ABC weapons, civil terror, deportations, etc. you would tradeoff the same costs with the military, political gains.

The new Russian activity in the Donbas has risen my probability forecast. However, I don't jump too high based on the observation that I haven't seen other Ukrainian public figures being kidnapped, assassinated, fleeing, etc. Perhaps these have happened, but it hasn't been on my radar so I ASSUME the chances of Volodymyr doing so as well is relatively low. I will probably never go below 2% because that seems like the average probability of dying in a single year.
0% Flee, but "cease" worries me if the Russians were to get lucky in an assignation attempt.
Its the long game.
Only if he is killed. He is not going to simply leave. A full scale assault by Russia leaves some probability of reaching him.
Seems very unlikely but this is war
US int will likely help protect him from targeted action. chance killing durging general bombardment or tactical nuclear blast seem most likely.
He is living in a war zone and the likely target of further assassination attempts and airstrikes.

My rationale is essentially the same the same question with a shorter timefreme. That is' I'm reducing my estimate from 20% on 26 Feb 21 to 1% to reflect the changes in the passage of time as well as Russia's ineptness at executing any sort of well formed strategy.
Сбежит .

Initial highly subjective forecast. Chance of fleeing is virtually 0%. Assassination or death by wider area military strike (e.g. missile strike) is the primary scenario for how Zelensky’s rule could end in the timeframe. I’ve added some probability beyond what I think true chances are (~10%) to reflect unknown unknowns in this extremely fluid situation. Putin also still has some unplayed cards.
war consitions might force him to
Chance of him being removed is decreasing, peace is coming in the west of ukraine

Odds of a natural death or internal political upheaval are negligible. Odds of assassination are probably around 1-2%. Odds of total Ukrainian military failure are much harder to estimate, but with Russia unable to even take Mariupol after about 2 months of fighting, I give it low single digits that Russia decisively defeats Ukraine in the next 7 months.
Initial forecast. A long time related to impact of the conflict. If there is "peace" he may have a different role as part of the settlement.
